{
  "texts": [
    "Working towards different interests increases the diversity within a system leading to a larger variety in its output.",
    "Hence, an institutionally diverse system is more resilient to risks and crises, being ready to move towards a wider range of alternative directions.",
    "Similarly, cultural diversity is important as it enriches the cultural meaning space of wider populations.",
    "Being exposed to an enriched cultural environment empowers people to become more creative and flexible in leading their lives in complex, dynamically changing, and globally interconnected cultures and societies [47].",
    "Media and cultural institutions can serve a diverse cultural environment as public value to individuals, society, and industry."
  ]
}